  "content": "Powerhouse provides the `OID` (Object ID) custom scalar type for unique identifiers in document models. Key patterns:\n\n- Objects in arrays must have an `id: OID!` field\n- IDs are generated in the **reducer** using `generateId()` from `document-model/core`, never passed from the UI\n- The `AddTodoItemInput` only requires `text`, not `id` - the reducer generates the ID\n- Update and delete operations require `id: OID!` to identify the target\n\n```typescript\nimport { generateId } from \"document-model/core\";\n\naddTodoItemOperation(state, action) {\n  const id = generateId();\n  state.items.push({ ...action.input, id, checked: false });\n}\n```\n\nThis pattern ensures unique, consistent IDs across all operations and keeps the operation input minimal.",
